  heroImage="/images/service-seo.webp"
  heroButtons={[
    { text: "Get a Free AI Visibility Audit", href: "/contact/", class: "btn btn-primary" },
    { text: "View Plans", href: "#pricing", class: "btn btn-secondary" }
  ]}
  whatsappText="Hi Jraft Creative, I'd like to learn about ChatGPT optimisation for my business in Singapore."
  ctaLabel="Ready to Get Started?"
  ctaTitle="Get Your Brand Into ChatGPT Answers"
  ctaDescription="Book a free audit and we'll show you exactly what ChatGPT says about your brand right now — and what it says about your competitors. We test real prompts your customers are asking and deliver a clear action plan. Response within 24 hours."
  ctaButtons={[
    { text: "Get a Free AI Visibility Audit", href: "/contact/", class: "btn btn-primary" },
    { text: "Chat on WhatsApp", href: "https://wa.me/6582234578?text=Hi%20Jraft%20Creative%2C%20I%27d%20like%20to%20learn%20about%20ChatGPT%20optimisation.", class: "btn btn-secondary" }
  ]}
>

  <aside class="canonical-pointer" style="padding: 0.875rem 1rem; background: rgba(57, 187, 157, 0.08); border-radius: 4px; margin: 1rem auto; max-width: 760px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #c4c4cc); line-height: 1.5;">
    Part of our full <a href="/geo-agency-singapore/" style="color: #39BB9D; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;">GEO agency Singapore</a> service — see the complete AI-search approach.
  </aside>

  <!-- ========== THE CHALLENGE ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="challenge" aria-label="Why businesses need ChatGPT optimisation">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">The Challenge</p>
        <h2>ChatGPT Has Become the New Recommendation Engine</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>ChatGPT has fundamentally changed how people discover businesses. Users no longer scroll through Google results — they ask ChatGPT directly: "best digital agency in Singapore", "top physiotherapist near Paya Lebar", "which CRM should I use". ChatGPT responds with a short list of 3-4 brands it considers credible. If your business isn't on that list, you're invisible to a rapidly growing audience that skips search engines entirely.</p>
        <p>The problem is that ChatGPT doesn't rank websites the way Google does. It evaluates entity signals — structured data, third-party mentions, review consistency, and content it can parse into direct answers. Most Singapore businesses have invested heavily in Google SEO but have done nothing to ensure ChatGPT can even identify their brand, let alone recommend it. The result is zero visibility on the platform <a href="/blog/why-ai-search-matters-singapore/">60.9% of Singaporeans</a> already use for everyday decisions.</p>
        <p>Meanwhile, your competitors who have optimised for ChatGPT are capturing the recommendations your customers should be seeing. Every prompt answered without your brand is a lead that goes to someone else. ChatGPT optimisation is no longer optional — it's a critical channel that sits alongside SEO, <a href="/ai-search-optimisation-agency-singapore/">AI search optimisation</a>, and paid ads in any serious digital strategy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== HOW CHATGPT RECOMMENDATION LOGIC WORKS ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="chatgpt-recommendation-logic" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="How ChatGPT decides which brands to recommend">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">How ChatGPT Works</p>
        <h2>How ChatGPT Decides Which Brands to Recommend</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>ChatGPT's recommendations aren't random. Understanding its recommendation logic is the first step to getting your brand cited. Here's how the system works — and why most businesses fail to appear in AI-generated answers without a dedicated <a href="/llmo-services-singapore/">LLMO strategy</a>.</p>

        <h3>Browsing Mode vs Training Data</h3>
        <p>ChatGPT operates in two modes. Without browsing, it relies entirely on patterns from training data (knowledge cutoff). With browsing enabled, it actively searches the web via Bing, retrieves current pages, and synthesises answers from live sources. Optimising for both modes requires strong training data presence AND current, structured web content. This is why <a href="/ai-visibility-singapore/">AI visibility</a> demands a dual strategy — you need to be present in the data ChatGPT was trained on and the sources it browses in real time.</p>

        <h3>Probabilistic Output</h3>
        <p>ChatGPT doesn't have a fixed "ranking list." Every response is probabilistic — there's less than a 1 in 100 chance it gives the exact same brand list if you ask the same question 100 times. This means ChatGPT optimisation is about increasing the probability your brand appears, not securing a fixed position. More signals = higher probability.</p>

        <h3>Trusted Sources</h3>
        <p>ChatGPT weights certain sources more heavily: review platforms (Google Reviews, Trustpilot, Clutch), industry directories, government registries, Wikipedia, and established media. Building your presence on these platforms directly increases your citation probability.</p>

        <h3>Entity Consistency</h3>
        <p>ChatGPT needs to resolve your brand as a single entity across all sources. Inconsistent naming, conflicting addresses, or contradictory service descriptions create ambiguity that reduces citation confidence. Structured data (schema markup) eliminates this ambiguity.</p>

        <div class="content-callout reveal">
          <p>ChatGPT recommends brands it can verify from multiple independent sources. The more consistent and widespread your entity signals, the more confidently ChatGPT names your business.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHAT WE DELIVER ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="sub-services" aria-label="ChatGPT optimisation services we deliver">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">What We Deliver</p>
        <h2>Everything You Need to Win ChatGPT Recommendations</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>We reverse-engineer how ChatGPT selects brands to recommend, then systematically build the signals your business needs to appear in those answers. Every tactic is designed specifically for ChatGPT's recommendation logic — not recycled Google SEO.</p>
        <p>Combine ChatGPT optimisation with our <a href="/services/seo-performance/">SEO services</a> for complete search coverage, or add <a href="/services/paid-ads/">paid ads</a> and <a href="/services/social-media/">social media</a> to build a full-funnel acquisition strategy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-details-grid">
        <div class="service-detail-card service-detail-card--overlay reveal reveal-d1" data-bg="/images/detail-seo-audit.webp">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>AI Visibility Audit</h3>
            <p>We test 20-30 real prompts your customers ask ChatGPT, document every response, and benchmark your brand against competitors. You'll see exactly where ChatGPT recommends you, where it recommends competitors, and where it ignores your industry entirely.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card service-detail-card--overlay reveal reveal-d2" data-bg="/images/detail-onpage-seo.webp">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Schema &amp; Entity Optimisation</h3>
            <p>ChatGPT needs to understand who you are before it can recommend you. We implement Organization, Service, FAQ, and Speakable schemas in JSON-LD, plus llms.txt files that give AI direct access to your brand information and service offerings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card service-detail-card--overlay reveal reveal-d3" data-bg="/images/detail-speed-vitals.webp">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Citation-Ready Content</h3>
            <p>Content formatted for how ChatGPT consumes information — answer-first paragraphs, structured comparison data, fact-dense descriptions, and FAQ blocks that map directly to the prompts your prospects type into ChatGPT every day.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card service-detail-card--overlay reveal reveal-d1" data-bg="/images/detail-analytics-reporting.webp">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Authority Building</h3>
            <p>ChatGPT cross-references your brand across review sites, directories, and authoritative publications before recommending you. We systematically build your presence on the sources ChatGPT trusts most — turning scattered mentions into consistent, recommendation-driving signals.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHY CHOOSE US ========== -->
