      </div>
      <div class="service-details-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));">
        <div class="service-detail-card reveal reveal-d1">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>ChatGPT-Specific Strategies</h3>
            <p>We don't apply generic SEO tactics and hope they work on ChatGPT. Our methodology is built around how ChatGPT's browsing, retrieval, and recommendation systems actually function — from training data patterns to real-time web access.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card reveal reveal-d2">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Real-Time Prompt Monitoring</h3>
            <p>We continuously test prompts your customers use and track whether ChatGPT recommends your brand, a competitor, or nobody. You get a live picture of your ChatGPT visibility — not a quarterly snapshot that's already outdated.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card reveal reveal-d3">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Singapore Market Focus</h3>
            <p>We understand how Singaporeans phrase prompts, which local directories ChatGPT references, and the competitive landscape across industries here. Our strategies are built for the Singapore market, not adapted from a global playbook.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-detail-card reveal reveal-d1">
          <div class="service-detail-card__content">
            <h3>Proven Citation Growth</h3>
            <p>We measure success by how often ChatGPT names your brand in response to target prompts. Our clients see measurable citation rate increases within 60-90 days, with compounding gains as authority signals strengthen over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== 10 PROMPTS SINGAPORE USERS ASK CHATGPT ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="chatgpt-prompts-singapore" aria-label="10 prompts Singapore users ask ChatGPT about businesses">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Real Prompts</p>
        <h2>10 Prompts Singapore Users Ask ChatGPT About Businesses</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content reveal">
        <p>These are real prompts Singapore consumers type into ChatGPT. For each one, we've noted what ChatGPT looks for when selecting brands to recommend.</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>"Best [industry] in Singapore"</strong> — ChatGPT looks for brands with strong review profiles and consistent entity data across multiple sources.</li>
          <li><strong>"Recommend a [service provider] near [area]"</strong> — Location signals matter: Google Business Profile, local directory listings, and address consistency.</li>
          <li><strong>"Which [service] should I use for my small business?"</strong> — ChatGPT favours brands with pricing transparency and clear service descriptions.</li>
          <li><strong>"Compare [Brand A] vs [Brand B] vs [Brand C]"</strong> — Comparison queries pull from review sites, feature pages, and structured comparison data.</li>
          <li><strong>"Is [brand name] good? Reviews?"</strong> — ChatGPT synthesises review sentiment across Google, Trustpilot, Clutch, and industry-specific platforms.</li>
          <li><strong>"How much does [service] cost in Singapore?"</strong> — Pricing pages with structured data get cited. Brands without visible pricing get skipped.</li>
          <li><strong>"Best [industry] for [specific need] in Singapore"</strong> — Niche queries reward specific service pages, FAQ schema, and detailed content.</li>
          <li><strong>"Who are the top [industry] agencies in Singapore?"</strong> — Authority signals dominate: industry awards, media mentions, directory rankings, client portfolios.</li>
          <li><strong>"[Service] vs doing it myself"</strong> — Educational content that compares DIY vs professional approaches gets cited for these queries.</li>
          <li><strong>"What should I look for in a [service provider]?"</strong> — Brands with "how to choose" content and evaluation criteria pages capture these queries.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="content-callout reveal">
          <p>These prompts represent real buying intent. If your brand doesn't appear in ChatGPT's answers for prompts like these, you're invisible to prospects who are ready to purchase.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

